Yll Gorani,2026-03-01,"Do not buy from Lenovo! I ordered a laptop and never received it. Instead of helping me track down my missing package or offering a replacement, Lenovo's customer service completely ignored me. It is obvious they only care about taking your money. Once the payment goes through, they disappear and take absolutely no responsibility to ensure the customer actually receives the product. No support, no accountability, and terrible communication. I had to fight just to get my own money back. Save yourself the headache and buy from a company that actually values its customers!"
Nicholas Collins,2026-02-26,"This was advertised as coming with a promotional item. I did not receive the promotional item. I have contacted Lenovo EVERY day since I saw the item was missing. They won't even SPEAK to me. They always say I have the wrong order number, the wrong department, the wrong this the wrong that. This is shady and deceptive. All I want is to please talk to a human. I bought your flagship item, does that not qualify me to speak with a human?"
Sunil Arshahil,2026-02-25,"The build quality is an absolute joke. Within months, the ""premium"" finish starts peeling, and the hinges—the most basic mechanical part of a laptop—feel like they were engineered out of recycled plastic spoons. Don't be surprised if your screen starts flickering or the keyboard decides that certain vowels are ""optional"" just after the return window closes.​Thermal Management: These machines run hotter than a backyard grill. You can’t even use it on your lap without risking a burn, and the fan noise sounds like a jet engine preparing for takeoff just to open a single browser tab.​Battery Life: The advertised ""all-day battery"" is a total myth. Expect it to plummet from 100% to ""Critical Alert"" the moment you unplug the charger.​The Service: A Black Hole of Bureaucracy​If the hardware is bad, the customer service is a catastrophe. Dealing with their support team is like shouting into a void.​The Infinite Loop: You’ll be bounced between departments, forced to repeat your serial number to five different people, only to be told that your very obvious hardware defect is ""software-related"" and not covered.​Repair Limbo: If you are ""lucky"" enough to get a repair authorized, kiss your laptop goodbye for weeks. They’ll ship it to a depot where it sits untouched, only to return it with the same issue—and perhaps a few new scratches for good measure.​The Warranty Scam: They look for every possible loophole to deny a claim. It’s clear their priority isn’t fixing your machine; it’s protecting their bottom line.​The Verdict​Buying a Lenovo is essentially paying for a high-priced paperweight and a headache. Save your money and your sanity—look literally anywhere else."
Berlina,2026-02-25,Purchased a laptop but in error. Returned it and have not received my refund d back yet. It’s been over a month. They keep giving me the run around saying it’s still in approval status. I ask for supervisor but they keep giving me the run around on that too! Don’t buy anything from these people.
Missy,2026-02-24,I ordered a tablet for my daughters bday and NO WHERE did it say someone had to sign for the package. I get a notice from UPS that a sig is required... NO ONE WILL BE HOME TO WAIT UNTIL THEY SHOW UP!! I call to change the address and I am told NO they cant and that I have to wait until UPS tires 2 or 3 times then WAIT again 5-7 days for a refund!!!
Debbie,2026-02-23,"I had configured a laptop on the Lenovo website and was about to order until I saw that it would take 3 weeks or more to deliver. Bear in mind that I had a complete configuration saved in my checkout basket. I decided to chat with them to see why it would take so long. The representative, Allison, asked me for my ID of the saved basket. She said to five her 2 minutes. After more than 5 minutes,  she said that it would take that long because I had configured my laptop. So, she came up with an existing build of which she claimed would meet my needs since it was close to my build. I wanted to compare my build to what she quoted, which was at least  $500+ less than the one I built. Unfortunately, it was 3 or more hours before I could do so. When I did, my saved basket was gone. Erased. I emailed Allison back to tell her that I could not believe that they would erase a consumers based but received no response. My guess is that they wanted to get rid of existing merchandise. I will not so business with a company that operates that way. Taking my money elsewhere."
dave,2026-02-23,the worst company the prepares support…the worst company the prepares support like to hang up on you this was my  first gaming pc and the last time l will by anything off Lenovo there page where you get there updates for the drives for desktop his been down for days l try to tell them 2 times yesterday the told me there was know  issue and l told  them there was the agent second force me to give the my serial number for my pc and  l told them  l do not have to give you this to you i'm this telling you that the page is down and they purposely hung up on me  I will not be buying anything  from a pc  monitors  mice laptops they  treat me like a trash pass this to your friends and family
gim smith,2026-02-23,"customer support is as bad as it gets, called 4 times to resolve a software issue, after talking to a babbling robot and answering an idiotic number of questions I....was either transferred to the wrong department who had the pleasure of routing me to another robot, another set of questions etc or, I had  absolute silence where I hung up after 5 minutes.  Next stop? Best Buy to return my levono tablet"
Scott M,2026-02-23,"I've purchased multiple products from Lenovo. Recently (2022) they introduced a reward program in Canada. (I was not aware). I made a purchase recently of a new computer, and during the purchase was told to signup for the Rewards program. I did---after I made the purchase I signed up. NOW I'm told, I am ineligible to get rewards on that purchase, because the Lenovo ""Policy"" states that I must sign up for the rewards program before the purchase, not immediatley afterward. That's a shite policy, and a complete rip-off to the consumer who just spent hundreds of dollars. Shame on Lenovo. Guess I'll be looking elsewhere for my next purchase, hopefully better customer service."
YES R,2026-02-23,"Purchased a new Lenovo Y25 display gaming screen and it was bad The USB port stopped working and I talk to the support they told me that they will give me a new one, but I have to send them my old one. That is with the broken ports, after that I received a used one and had a lot of scratches and also the ports stopped working after one month.They told me that they can’t support me anymore because of the warranty limit.After that, I think I will stop recommending any lenovo project. Because of the poor quality and poor customer service."
Mrs. G,2026-02-22,Bought Lenovo laptop during pandemic time and it still works😂
Ms Leeja,2026-02-21,I ordered a phone and  phone was never opened. I returned it with prior authorization.It’s been months and still no refund. I provided proof it was delivered to their warehouse. Still no refund. I’ve contacted customer service numerous times only to be told “they are working on it.” It is past the point of ridiculousness. I want my refund. I cannot recommend ordering directly from Lenovo.
Richard Lebovitz,2026-02-21,"I purchased a Legion 7i on sale. When it arrived it was missing the second SSD, which was clearly specified on the invoice and item description.I contacted sales support and was told that the issue was software - the SSD needed ""activation"". They also told me that if there was an issue I could return the unit for a new one.  I was transferred to technical support and they confirmed that the unit was missing the SSD. I was transferred back to customer service who told me I that I could return the unit for a refund and would have to order a new one if I wanted to replace it. They advised me to talk with Sales and then transferred me there. This process so far was almost two hours. Sales tried to sell me a completely different model, at a price higher than the local retailers. To correct this they could have just replaced the unit, or sent the missing hard drive, but it seems that customer service is not the highest priority for Lenovo."
jake Kipkertich,2026-02-21,"Whether you are a corporate executive, a competitive gamer, or a student, Lenovo’s 2026 models prioritize balance—specifically pairing processing power with significant gains in battery efficiency."
Dan,2026-02-19,Laptops are good.
Bassel Chakhachiro,2026-02-18,"I am extremely disappointed with my recent experience with Lenovo. I placed an order for a standard IdeaPad laptop on December 27th, with an original delivery date of February 5th. Since then, the delivery date has been pushed back multiple times — first to March, and now all the way to May 30th. That means a total waiting time of five months for a non‑custom product, which is completely unacceptable.Throughout this process, I have had to repeatedly contact Lenovo myself to get any form of update. Each time I reached out, I received vague promises or shifting timelines, but never a concrete solution. Even when I filed a formal complaint, the only response I received was yet another delay and a suggestion to “contact us again after delivery” to discuss compensation. That is not how customer service should work.What makes this even more concerning is that I have seen many similar complaints online, including on Reddit, from customers facing the same extreme delays and lack of support. This suggests a broader issue with Lenovo’s logistics and communication.I expected far better from a global brand. The lack of transparency, the constant shifting of delivery dates, and the absence of proactive support have left me with the impression that Lenovo does not take its customers seriously. At this point, I am genuinely reconsidering whether I will ever purchase from Lenovo again."
Brian,2026-02-18,"Absolutely atrocious customer service.  I ordered a 5G tablet,  but got the non 5G model. Lenovo mistake,  not mine so I asked could they send the correct model.  They said best they can do is cover the cost of me sending back the incorrect one, refunding me fully and then ne ordering a new one. Ie order another 5G, be sent the incorrect one again. Tablet was returned,  and ill be going for a brand other than Lenovo.  Lost a customer and I highly suggest others avoid Lenovo because of their atrocious customer service,  especially when Lenovo screwed up"
Bhekisile Jozi,2026-02-18,"It's been hardly two years since I bought two Lenovo laptops for my daughter and me. Both are in bad quality, as screens are opening up and hinges are falling off, making it difficult to close and open the laptop. Now the charger also is not functioning properly; it is on and off. I'll never buy Lenovo again."
