Victor,2026-02-15,"Previous laptop was HP and gave excellent performance until I spilled coffee on the keyboard. Purchased Lenovo Idea Pad because of price. However the screen  jumps when the mouse is too precise when I hover over the mouse pad and also  you have to touch the mousepad in the exact position (either lower corner) to move on otherwise nothing happens. When typing an email, not all keypad letters respond when touched  and the text jumps to another line and does not make any sense when reading back. Can't wait for my H.P. to be repaired."
Miguel Ramirez,2026-02-27,"On 15 December 2025, I returned a Lenovo Legion laptop (€1,527.03) via PostNL to their Eindhoven facility. Despite having full proof of delivery and providing it to them on Jan 5, 15, 22, and 26, Lenovo ignored to refund within 14 days.For two months, I was met with scripted excuses: ""logistics is searching"" or ""wait 3–5 business days."" When they finally issued a refund in February 2026, they arbitrarily withheld €71.62.If you have an issue, do not wait for their ""investigations."" Document everything and file a formal dispute (Geschillencommissie in the Netherlands) immediately.Because of this unprofessional handling and the financial strain it caused, I will never buy from Lenovo again, nor can I recommend them to anyone. If you value your time, your money, and your peace of mind, look elsewhere."
Scottie Wyatt,2026-02-13,"I purchased 5 Thinkstation P3 Machines in Dec 2024, every single one will not update to Windows 25H2.  Support tells me its not there problem, it's a Microsoft issue.  They made the product, it's THERE problem.  They refuse to do anything"
John,2026-02-12,"Purchased a laptop online and trying to ship it to a different billing address was an absolute nightmare. They kept telling me it was my credit card company that declined it but when I called Discover, they told me they never seen anything from Lenovo even though I tried three times.They finally shipped the laptop, but i also ordered a docking station which was not shipped and after waiting a week I called them to see what the problem was. they told me they have to escalate a customer service and it’s gonna take 24 hours to find out why it has not shippedThis was my first and last order from the Lenovo. I  will never order from these clowns again."
Dale McFarland,2026-02-11,"This rating must go below 1.0 STARS! Computer quality down the drain. I bought a new Dell XPS 15 (""best laptop we make"") a year ago after my prior version got fat (full) and slow. The new version was/is garbage and required endless hours with Indian tech experts (laugh) to attemp fixing the many flaws. I sent it back for repairs and a software reinstallation as suggested. They sent it back having ignored the problems aand nothing had changed. I bought a Lenovo (remember IBM) ThinkPad (""best laptop we make"") in September as i needed a reliable computer and had to move on with business. It also had a bunch of flaws like a black screen that pops up every 55 seconds and a cursor that moves around the page while typing. Ever place a stock order and the computer screen goes black? And you lose the price of the computer in 10 seconds because you couldn't see the screen or ticker movement? Lenovo laughed when i told them about this. I explained how annoying it is to have to click a button evry 55 seconds because my screen goes black. We've been resetting hibernation and sleep timer to ""NEVER"" (YouTube Videos too) for months and reinstalling and updating drivers endlessly. They have no idea how to stop their computer from shutting off the screen and now they won't shedule discussions of repair/return/exchange. Then I saw their TrustPiltot rating is now 1.3 STARS! That is the same as Dell when i decided to cut my losses!! 1.3 STARS!!! BAD! I have two new computers that have cost me well over $20K apiece by now. Do NOT give your money to these companies. Let's get those ratings down below 1.0....please!! Give me a laugh....i need it. I am writing to warn consumers just how bad the scammer movement is in the IT market. Is their a quality manufacturer of anything? Samsung S-25 phone garbage, drops call, etc for $1200. More hours in line or on the phone. Be careful where you get upsold to ""the best"" because it won't be. Love each other. God blesses us so we can be a blessing to others!"
Braulio Lopez,2026-02-10,"Worst customer service ever.I purchased a ThinkPad X9 15” directly from Lenovo’s website. Before I even received the laptop, the price on Lenovo.com dropped. I contacted customer service to request a price match, but the sales representative refused to honor Lenovo’s own lower price.I asked to speak with a supervisor. Instead of transferring me, the representative claimed to speak with a supervisor on my behalf and said the request was denied. When I insisted on speaking directly with a supervisor, I was told none were available. This made it seem like customer service was either being dishonest or supervisors simply did not want to deal with unhappy customers.I was then told the only way to get the lower price was to receive the laptop, return it for a refund, and place a new order. Lenovo would rather force customers through an unnecessary and inconvenient return process than apply a simple price adjustment or credit.This directly contradicts Lenovo’s own Price Guarantee policy, which states that price adjustments are valid within 30 days when the lower price is advertised on Lenovo.com. The lower price I requested was from Lenovo’s own website, not a competitor.Extremely disappointing experience."
Gabriel,2026-02-10,"WORST BRAND I EVER BOUGHT . RABBER UNDER THE SCREEN CAME OFF. SCREEN BROKE AFTER FEW TIMES CLOSING THE SCREEN (FOLDING IT) . I WILL NEVER BUY LENOVO AGAIN EVEN IF YOU GIVE IT FOR FREE . AS SOON AS I GET MONEY I LL BUY ANYTHING ELSE EXCEPT THIS **** . AND THE ONE I ALREADY HAVE, I WILL SIMPLY THROW IT OUT THE WINDOW ."
ELAINE,2026-02-10,I have a ideapad there is a problem with the keyboard they said I had damaged it from a photo i have not damaged my laptop very poor service
James Barnhart,2026-02-10,"I would give Lenovo ZERO, but it is not an option.  I went online to order a tablet needed it quickly What was chosen was to be delivered by February 9, 2026.  I called and spoke with ANDERSON in customer support to make sure everything correct and would be a smooth transaction.  Completed my order with ANDERSON.  No one at any time told me it would not arrive on February 9 or that I had to sign for the tablet and accessories.  I paid and waited.  I finally received notice of shipment on February 9 to deliver on February 11.  This is when I found out that a signature is required.  I would have shipped to work if someone had advised me.   I called Lenovo and the girl advised they did not put signature required on UPS did.  I called UPS To remove signature requirement or redirect package and was advised Lenovo blocked all changes and that Lenovo would have to make delivery change.  I called Lenovo again and was told Lenovo puts signature required on all orders over $200 per their website. I advised the man that my order was only $179 and did not even make$200 threshold.  He advised sorry there is nothing he can do.  He would not let me speak to a supervisor or management either to try to resolve Lenovos misrepresentation and misinformation or lack thereof.   So now I am out a tablet that cannot be delivered, out my $ and will have to fight to get a refund.   NEVER EVER BUY LENOVO!!!  You have been warned."
nima azodi,2026-02-10,"I ordered a legion go 2 some time last year that was supposed to be delivered on the 5th of January 2026, signed for delivery.Got a notification to say it had been delivered whilst at work - no signature, a picture of a box in front of a pair of legs. Not even my door.Have been in touch Lenovo since the 5th of January and not even their formal complaints team respond to emails and specialists on the phone refer to email.So now I am taking legal action through Section 75 and contacting the ombudsman. NEVER EVER SPEND MONEY WITH THIS COMPANY. In the UK we have the Financial Ombudsman that ensures companies adhere to the Consumer Rights act of 2025 and the distance selling regulation - a fact that Lenovo seems oblivious of.They even asked me to get a crime reference number, which I did and they confirmed in writing that upon sharing his they would process my refund within 5-7 days.... day 10 and still nothing. not a word. not a peep.I am now litigating for loss of earnings due to time spent on this matter."
Ahmed,2026-02-06,"Omg, where do I start with this company. Everything about this company sucks, especially their customer service. I ordered a monitor, and now after two months I am still waiting for it and I don't even know the status of it. I literally called 11 times, and not only that but they took money from my account and I can't even cancel the order because they have to wait to confirm my order. Customer service sucks, order status sucks, everything. Do not go at all costs"
Gabriel Adelin,2026-02-06,"Headline: Premium Care is a joke – Hardware failure met with ""bed surface"" excusesReview:""I am extremely disappointed with the so-called 'Premium Care' service. My laptop’s GPU (RTX 4070) is hitting 87°C, causing massive thermal throttling and FPS drops, making the device unusable for its intended purpose.Instead of honoring the 'On-site Support' and 'Next Business Day' intervention I paid for, the support team wasted my time with ridiculous scripts. They actually asked if I'm using the laptop on a mattress, completely ignoring the technical evidence and photos showing critical temperature levels.It’s unacceptable to pay for a premium service only to be treated like a novice and forced to threaten with Consumer Protection (ANPC) just to get a technician scheduled. Expectations were high, but the actual support experience is at rock bottom. If you value your time and hardware, be wary of their 'Premium' promises.Model: Lenovo Legion (RTX 4070)Service Type: Premium Care"""
James Fuller,2026-02-06,"The website said free and fast shipping. Then it shipped from China.   Nothing on the website or ordering process said it was going to ship from China. I could have ordered from a local supplier for the same price and had it by now.Then they sold me an on site repair that is useless to me. It wasn't optional, no was to opt out."
David Reid,2026-02-06,I sent a expensive monitor back under the refund process its now been almost a month without my refund being processed. I keep getting told by customer service its not reached the main warehouse and I need to wait even though its passed there refund timeframe.The service is shocking I will never order anything from them again.
Kelly Jackson,2026-02-06,"I would give @Lenovo a zero-star rating if I was able.  I purchased the Lenovo Slim 7 Pro X laptop about a year ago.  I didn’t use it for roughly 3-months after because I was using my work PC.  Definite error on my part but I was very short on time.  When I do begin using it, it malfunctioned pretty immediately (within 2-weeks).  It would power on and off but the screen would either go black shortly after starting it or wouldn’t do anything at all (remained black but the keyboard had backlights so I knew it was on).  Lenovo required me to send it back.  They worked on it for a couple weeks, sent it back to me, and nothing had improved.  Lenovo had me send it back again, they worked on it for a couple weeks and again returned it to me.  This time it worked for roughly 6-8 months.  Just enough time for the warranty to expire.  They did try to upsell me on the warranty pretty hard during my first two repair incidents.  Since I have never had any major issues with my prior PC’s (other brands), I declined.  Mistake #2 on my part.Now, the machine is having the same issues as before.  I purchased a 30-day Live Service package.  I called them within 24 hours to get my machine serviced.  They told me they only provide software service, and I need hardware service.  I paid about $120 for the service so they told me to call another number to have the incorrectly purchased service refunded so I could instead buy the warranty upgrade.  Sat on the phone for 30 minutes to be told they don’t give refunds - even though the service was not used, and will not fix my problem - on a machine barely 1-year old that has already fully malfunctioned 3 times.In summary, this is not only the WORST PC I have EVER used, @Lenovo is also the WORST CUSTOMER SERVICE I have ever experienced for a relatively high-end/expensive purchase.Keep your sanity and buy from another provider…DO NOT BUY FROM LENOVO!"
Jackie Bsharah,2026-02-05,"I bought a Lenovo Yoga 9.1 for more than $2000. I have used it for less than a week, and I can't get the websites to load. I called customer service and was told I needed to pay $69 for assistance. I have had the device for about a week! When I called to share the experience so the company could take action, I was told they needed permission before they could transfer me to someone I could file a complaint with. I have decided to make my complaint public rather than be transferred again and placed on hold. I would avoid Lenovo, both for product issues and poor customer service."
F L,2026-02-04,"I tried to cancel an order and the chat bot demanded a 10-digit order number that my order number, copy-and-pasted, wasn't good enough for. I found a link to cancel the order instead and instead of cancelling the order I was told I would hear from them within three days about the status of the order. There is no option to chat with a human."
Ron Berezowski,2026-02-03,"Bought a lighted sound bar from Lenovo Pro for Business Canada.  Used Lenovo Rewards and money.  Item was shipped, never arrived at my office, was refused delivery somewhere and returned by UPS to Lenovo.  Got an email with that info, stating refunds for money and rewards would be done shortly.  Two and a half months later, four phone calls, no resolution.  Each time customer rep said they were upgrading and migrating their refund system, and to expect refund within five to seven business days.  Exact same response each time.  Each rep promised they would escalate my issue and get it resolved quickly.  Easy to make promises, but it seems Lenovo can't process a refund ever.  No way to escalate on the phone, no managers available.  Exceptionally poor service, I have stopped buying Lenovo products for the schools I provide IT services to.  Buyer beware if you ever need a refund, just wave bye-bye to your money..."
