D. N.,2026-01-21,They make you go in circles to get your refund. Do some research. So many cases online of this happening. Start a chargeback asap if you ever have to deal with this.
Nick,2026-01-20,"Placed an order with Lenovo for delivery on a certain day the following week.On the day before the delivery, I received an email from Lenovo that the order was delayed but they would try to fulfill it within the next THIRTY days.Customer care was not able to do anything other than cancel the order.Avoid Lenovo at all costs."
Clement Wong,2026-01-18,"Removes negative reviews on website, sayiing that my review do not meet their website ""guidelines"". My review was negative for their very poor customer service. Staff not responsive to issues and does not return call as promised or follow up on email. Compared to Dell and HP, Lenovo really needs to up its game with customer service. Call centre is outsourced and staff does not seem to care. Once call is hung up you would be lucky to hear from them again despite repeated promise."
Nicholas Kostik,2026-01-18,"The worst customer support staff on the planet. I have brandnew tablet from lenovo.com still in the UPS box before the 30 days. 20 daily calls later, and more than 10 hours wasted, I am still at ground zero. I hope Trump tarrifs this terrible company."
Obyn,2026-01-17,"If not for my daughter asking for Lenovo, I'll stay away from this company as best I can. They will give you a shipping date when you order and won't hear anything from them for over a week until you call up only to inform you it has not been shipped yet and there will be a delay. The customer service will give you a spiel for the shipping delay. I placed the order with the date of shipping in mind as necessary. If Lenovo cannot comply neither be courteous enough to email you of what is going on without you hounding them for the info, they should not give a shipping date they cannot abide with. It's as if they can deliver the order on time as per shipping date they give you, only to find out they only want your business and discard you after your order has been secured. Sure, they have an option for cancellation. After waiting for over a week? No courtesy to let you know immediately after placing the order when exactly it will shipped? My time to place an order somewhere else has been wasted by Lenovo already. I can only stretch my patience at this time and wait until kingdom come. It's my 2nd time ordering from them and nothing has changed since July of 2025."
Nick Pal,2026-01-16,WORSE ELECTRONICS COMPANY EVER FOR PROCESSING REFUNDS. IT IS NOW ONE MONTH AND I'M STILL WAITING FOR MY REFUND. DO NOT EVER BUY FROM THEM UNLESS YOU ARE 100% SURE YOU ARE KEEPING THE GOODS OTHERWISE EXPECT TO PULL YOUR HAIR WITH CUSTOMER SERVICE.
Felix Ocasio,2026-01-15,"I purchased a power bank for the legion go and after 4 days of purchase I never received any shipping details and when I called customer service (4times)to ask about my order, each rep  gave me a different response about the shipping details and after 5 days of waiting I ended up cancelling my order and decided to go with a different vendor."
Javier,2026-01-14,"I’m writing this to warn anyone considering buying directly from Lenovo Spain.Order: Lenovo ThinkPad T14 Gen 6 (AMD)Total paid: €2,050.11Order date: 20 Dec 2025Payment method: bank transfer (Wire Transfer)Before I paid, I asked Lenovo Sales/Customer Support to confirm delivery timing because I urgently needed the laptop for work and I was only going to be in Spain until early January. I was explicitly told the delivery would be between 2 and 6 January. That delivery window was the only reason I placed the order.Lenovo’s own order confirmation also showed estimated shipping/delivery between 02/01 and 06/01.What actually happened:- 20 Dec: I paid the full amount by bank transfer exactly as instructed (correct beneficiary/IBAN and the order number included as payment reference). I have a bank Proof of Payment (POP). Despite payment being made, Lenovo later claimed they had not received the funds.- 26 Dec: Lenovo emailed saying their records showed no payment received, and instructed me to send the POP to their payments email. I sent the POP again immediately.- 30 Dec: I called Lenovo three times because nothing was moving and the delivery window was approaching fast. On the first call (agent name: Mohammed), I was told to send the POP again (for the third time). After I resent it, I received the standard response: “wait 3–5 business days.” I called again to confirm receipt. I was told they had it, and again: “wait 3–5 business days.” I called again and got the same vague answer. No accountability, no urgency, no escalation.- Lenovo then sent an email stating the shipment was delayed. Still no firm solution, no new delivery date, and no meaningful explanation.At this point, the promised delivery window (2–6 January) was essentially impossible to meet, and I urgently needed a laptop. Lenovo’s internal failure to reconcile a basic bank transfer forced me into the only reasonable choice:- I cancelled the order through Customer Support to no avail, even when they confirmed that my order had been cancelled.- I cancelled the order through Lenovo’s own order page because Lenovo could not (or would not) confirm receipt of a valid payment and could not ensure delivery as promised.After cancellation, Lenovo still continued the same pattern:- Confirmed the order was cancelled, then asked me again for the Proof of Payment (POP) “to proceed with the refund.”- Offered “replacement order / reinstatement” as an option even though I clearly wanted a refund.- Provided no concrete refund timeline, just more back-and-forth and repeated requests for documentation that had already been provided multiple times.This was not a “courier delay” or a “stock issue.” This was a basic administrative failure:- I paid.- I provided evidence repeatedly.- Lenovo didn’t process it.- Lenovo delayed shipping.- I cancelled because Lenovo’s failure made the order pointless.- And now the refund is not handled immediately, which is unacceptable when the order is cancelled and the payment is already proven.My advice: DO NOT (I REPEAT, DO NOT) BUY DIRECTLY FROM LENOVO'S ONLINE STORE if you need reliability. If anything goes wrong — especially with bank transfer payments — you may end up stuck in an endless loop of “send the POP again” and “wait 3–5 business days,” with thousands of euros on the line.I am now pursuing formal complaints through consumer protection channels to recover money that should have been refunded promptly."
Robert Davis,2026-01-14,"I’ve been using a Lenovo Yoga laptop for everyday work, browsing, and media, and overall it’s been a good experience. The screen and build quality are strong, and it’s held up well with regular use. Performance has been more than enough for what I need, and it feels more premium than a lot of similarly priced laptops.The only downside has been some of Lenovo’s preinstalled software and updates, which can be a little annoying or unnecessary. Once that’s cleaned up, though, the machine itself runs smoothly and reliably.Overall it’s been a dependable laptop and I’d consider Lenovo again based on real-world use."
Alec Vardanian,2026-01-11,"I had canceled an order that was delayed, the cancelation was confirmed by Lenovo Spain on October 31, but the money (4500 euros) was never returned.I have been calling and emailing for 12 weeks now, and keep getting empty promises."
Rhett,2026-01-10,"I bought two Legion R24s monitors and one of them didn't come with a power cord.I tried to contact support via phone and the customer service line never even connected.The worthless AI chat bot on their forums couldn't direct me to a live agent because it kept looping asking me for a product and then eventually just froze and errored out.You can't even submit feedback for their complete lack of customer service, because the Submit  button on the feedback form doesn't even work!I've seen some bad customer service with computer equipment before, but this is beyond the worst I have ever seen."
