Edward Forgacs,2026-01-10,"Ordered an X1 2-in-1 costing over $3600 AUD. Lenovo ""moderated"" my unfavorable review so I'm re-posting it here:Unit shipped died within 2 hours of arrival. Didn't make it past the first reboot after the Windows welcome process. How's that for quality control? Clearly this unit did not have any meaningful burn-in testing which would be expected from a major manufacturer. It took over 3 weeks to get a refund for the DOA laptop and over 4 weeks from the date the order was placed, Lenovo have still not refunded the accessory charger which ordered with the unit (which was the wrong model). Lenovo are now making excuses about the delivery date for the replacement unit which was re-ordered, and it still hasn't shipped. There is no sign whatsoever that an attempt has been made to expedite the replacement despite repeated promises. Most calls and emails have not been returned. The customer service has been excruciating at every single step, from the pre-order sales team every step of the way through this process. The matter has now been referred by Lenovo to their ""ACL team"". Overall experience rating would be minus 10."
