George Canon,2026-01-08,"If I could rate them less than one star, I would. Watched some interviews with Lenovo execs at CES and how they were touting their AI and technology. I have a Lenovo AI PC and decided to give their AI Now a try. It's ok, as is the laptop, but I also decided to get a 4 yr subscription to their Smart Performance package, it was a relatively ok deal.Keep in mind, I purchased a subscription to software that I already had installed on my computer. After my card was successfully charged, I received an email some 10 minutes later stating I should expect delivery of my purchase in 2 days! What? The email included a link to ""Manage Subscription"", which I clicked on. No record of the order at all. Contacted support thru chat. OH NO! The chatbot only allows you to proceed if you have a valid order number (which they sent me, but they don't recognize it). So no go with that. Went to New Sales and they finally transferred me to ""customer support"", and they couldn't give me any help at all. Just said it takes 2 days. So I guess I'll have to wait for Elmer to get around to placing the ""Approved"" rubber sticker on the paperwork so their email system can send me a code.Wasn't the CEO on stage with Jensen Wong and Lisa Su chatting up how great Lenovo is? Do they really want to associate themselves and their companies with Lenovo's 1985 technology? And 8088 would be fine to run their platform I'm thinking."
Silvana,2026-01-07,I'm surprise for the great service received online. It was a little long process but we solved the problem.  Than for the mouse they fixed an appointment after few days and the tecnic comes at my office and fixed the problem. I'm very satisfied.
Deen Chowdhury,2026-01-07,"I am compelled to raise serious concerns regarding Lenovo’s handling of a refund for a returned laptop. The device was returned on 12 December 2025, with Yodel delivery confirmation provided to Lenovo. Despite clear evidence of return, no refund has been issued to date.Multiple phone calls and written follow-ups have failed to produce any explanation for the delay or a timeline for resolution. In the meantime, I am incurring ongoing credit card interest for a product that was returned and is no longer in my possession.The absence of communication, ownership, and accountability in this matter is unacceptable and reflects poorly on Lenovo’s after sales governance. I am sharing this publicly to highlight the issue at a senior level and to caution other customers to exercise care when ordering, particularly where returns and refunds are concerned."
Loops,2026-01-06,"Purchased Yoga Book 9i in Spring 2025 from Lenovo website. The number of add-ons they offer at the time of purchase is not user-friendly. Initially loved the 2-screen lightweight design (much lighter than the Asus 2-screen option). Odd how the charger was getting hot while brand new. Odd how the on-screen keypad didn’t always display. Deeply regret not returning immediately. Horrid customer service. Lenovo has been heavily marketing the “in-home repair” add-on (which I refused to buy) - has this company been deliberately causing glitches so that I would buy the add-on??? Laptop stopped working altogether while not on charge. I drove over 3-hours to get the battery replaced at Ameritech within a few months of purchase (not including phone time). Graphics issues have worsened & the video is constantly freezing, requiring shutdown about twice every tv episode (this laptop is currently at less than 9 months of light usage). USB adaptors also don’t seem to work in the ports. The screen configurations are jammy & the device is generally slow compared to both Asus & Apple (slower than my 2014 MacBook even though specs are supposedly much faster). I did a complete local reinstall & set it up again as a new PC. Same issues. Today Lenovo told me to take it to their “geek squad” at Best Buy. The lady answering the “geek squad” ph had zero knowledge. I am over it, ready to throw it in the garbage. What a rip-off, especially given the high price. I have spent hours & hours of my time on a new laptop with no end in site - one star if any.The only decent thing Lenovo could do now is let me return for a full refund.[Side-note: I now somewhat regret being mad at Apple for phasing out updates on my 2014 Macbook (which never had an issue & still works except Microsoft), & for selling me an Iph with a dud camera.]"
Mauricio Bogota,2026-01-05,"The worst service ever, I had a very poor experience with Lenovo’s post-sales and refund process. My order was never successfully delivered due to carrier issues (UPS), was returned to Lenovo, and Lenovo themselves confirmed in writing that a refund would be initiated.Despite this, the refund was not executed within the communicated timeframes. I spent weeks contacting customer support, repeatedly explaining the same situation, while receiving contradictory answers from different agents. The case was constantly shifted between “investigation,” “warehouse review,” and “carrier follow-up,” with no clear ownership or accountability.Even after Lenovo confirmed the order was returned and later classified as lost during the return process, the refund continued to be delayed with no concrete execution date or transaction reference provided in a timely manner.This experience shows a serious lack of internal coordination between customer support, warehouse, billing, and logistics. As a customer, I was left without the product and without the money for an unreasonable amount of time.I do not recommend Lenovo if you expect reliable customer support or timely refunds when issues arise."
Tahir Hussain,2026-01-04,"5 Star service- Regular Customer Long Term Customer,"
Rusan Mohammed,2026-01-02,"I can’t this recommend PS8: I purchased the Lenovo PS8 2TB external SSD and used it for normal file transfers. While copying around 60 GB of data continuously, the SSD becomes very hot. This level of heating is concerning for long-term use and data safety. Performance is acceptable, but thermal management could be better. Buyers who plan large or frequent data transfers should be aware of this heating issue before purchasing."
XALOR_EZ,2025-12-30,"i wish i could put 0 stars. this is far and away the worst customer service experience ive had buying something online. customer support has been terrible. 0 out of 10 would never recommend. my order took over 1 month just for them to cancel the order for no apparent reason. also, no supervisor or escelation ever available. they say they will contact you in 24 hours and this never happens. im filling official complaints aginst this business."
Alpesh Maradiya,2025-12-30,The product not worth and Customer Service sucks. The advisors are not at all concerned and blaming the consumers for choosing lenovo. If the prodcluct is defective still the staff would not assist. Products and services are not as per market standards.
Ignacio Aguilar,2025-12-29,"I placed an order at a supposed 35 percent discount. I submitted it and it ""auto refreshed the page and knocked it to a 22 percent discount. About 250 dollars more expensive. I sent emails with copy pastes of the receipts and carts from before and after. The sales rep sounded helpful, and said that should be enough, but after three weeks, the customer service dept. responded and said that unless I have screenshots with the full URL, they can't do anything. Terrible. If I could take stars away...."
Laurence Brown,2025-12-29,"Keyboard rendering two year old Yoga unusable.....This major issue began just before the end of the two year warrantly. I have to type TWO as I have no number key functioning. Intermittent keys just not working - which means I have now rely on Hello to even log in. So no good at work, as sometimes I'm unable to login at all. No Character keys work at all.Useless. Everything tried. Hactory reset... hard thirty second reset seems to get the number keys working again for a short while. Driver updates. Vacuuming keys, tried all actions... etc etc.Nothing spilt on it, not dropped. The OSK works perfectly.Now of course its out of warranty - thank you Currys for offering to look at it - just look at it for a princely Fifty pounds - the Pound key doesn't work of course, and I cannot bracket that, as those keys don't work either.56 - here you see, these are the only two number keys that work. All of the others are useless.The D key just fell off after a couple of months anyway. I gave up on getting it to stay on.This all began during warranty, but I kept thinking I could fix it. Now its too late.It's an appalling quality issue. Not worth repairing as the cost outweighs the value.Desperately bad quality - which is a shame, as it's quite a nice laptop. Just unusable in nay work situation where I need reliable access and functionality.Essentially I seriously regret this purchase, and am unable to recommend a Levono Yoga to anyone."
Rúben G.T.,2025-12-29,"I cancelled my Lenovo order a few hours after it was placed.The cancellation was then confirmed by phone when i got in touch with a support agent, but the laptop was still shipped 3 days later.It was never delivered to me and was returned within Lenovo’s logistics chain through UPS.For a month I’ve been told that a refund would be issued in 3–5 days after the package gets back to Lenovo, and that I would receive an email, but no emails ever arrived, and there are no written support channels (no email, no chat).Everything is by phone only, for limited week hours, and each call repeats the same assurances without resolution.The laptop has always been in Lenovo’s possession for a month now, from China to Portugal and back to the Netherlands, yet I still have neither the product nor a refund.I have now opened an internal refund request with my payment provider, still undergoing at the moment.I’m sharing this so others may be aware of the extreme challenges that are faced around cancellations and refunds when things don’t go as expected from the start."
Timmy Jones,2025-12-29,Note… Follow up reviewLenovo laptop motherboard went out on a computer that was 11 months old still under factory warranty…. It took 20 days to send from Micro Center Dallas to 5 hours down the road to Houston TX Lenovo center for repairs…. Lenovo did not know when they would be able to receive in the replacement motor board with the NIVIDA 4090 graphics card… Lenovo Customer Care center made final decision to replace the Laptop with an upgraded latest laptop…. Thanks Lenovo for replacing the laptop with the latest 5090 NIVIDA graphics card and updated memory etc…. the major issue it took numerous phone calls… 58 days before I received in the replacement computer……
Shane,2025-12-29,"They remove your review if it not 5 star, thus the mostly positive review on their website are fake."
Michael,2025-12-26,"I ordered a desktop computer with software add ons for MS Office and McAfee internet protection.  Computer arrived and was very easy to set up.HOWEVER, I didn’t receive the product download key for the McAfee sorfware.  Called after-market support. After 20+ minutes in chat got connected.  CSR was unvable to resolve.  They entered escalation and told me I’d be contacted in 25-48 business hours. That did  not happen.Called again, long wait time, and another promise for resolution in 24-48 hours which DID NOT happen.Eac time I spoke with after market support I asked for a refund of the McAffee sortware purchase Ute they insisted that to do that I would need to return the entire purchase.I felt this requirement was was crap since it’s just a software product key, which I kept stating.I finally contacted McAfee directly and they resolved the issue on the spot.I put. In a dispute with the credit card company because the McAfee purchase was a separate line item from the computer.Finally 2 weeks later Lenovo sent me the product key but I don’t think I should pay because I went to McAfee direct to get an annual subscription.Bottom line, seriously reconsider purchasing software with your Lenovo computer. Purchase it separately because their aftermarket support for any software related issues is horrible"
Eric,2025-12-25,"Lenovo also sensors incoming reviews when customers reports poor customer service. That is why they get 1 star, down from 3.Delivery time postponed several times after order was placed. Poor customer service, no will to investigate delays from web chat customer service, impossible to get through to customer phone support."
Louise Bartels,2025-12-24,"Never again will I order anything from Lenovo. The (non-existent) customer service of this company is absolutely unsatisfactory and completely unacceptable.At the end of November, I ordered two laptops (gifts for my kids), a Microsoft Family license, and a pen. Well over €2100. First issue: the license never arrived. I was supposed to receive a key via email — nothing. When I finally made it through the endless chat filter, I was so fed up I cancelled the license right then and there (in the chat — no other option). A week later, I got my money back. So far, so okay.Then it turned out that both laptops already came with a pen, so I wanted to return the extra one — I don’t need three, thank you. I requested a return on December 4. Nothing happened. On December 5 I contacted chat again, asking where my return label was — should be simple, right? The agent said: “It should arrive soon, 2–3 business days max.” Of course, it didn’t.On December 9, I checked in again. This time they told me the label would be sent by post. Sorry, what?! BY POST?! What century are we in? Oh no, wait — by email after all (probably a translation glitch or something, since all agents appear to be based in Pakistan or India, working with standardized scripts and AI-generated translations).Another 2–3 business days, another thousand apologies. “Everything will be fine.” Not. I went through the same circus again on December 11 and 15. Same scripted apologies, and now the agent claimed they would “personally take care of my case” and guaranteed the label would arrive within 5 business days. You guessed it: nothing came.At this point — nearly ten days later — I’ve given up.Lenovo’s return process? It simply doesn’t exist. You’d better be very sure of what you’re ordering, because returning anything is virtually impossible. I would love to rant loudly about this company, but that would probably get my review rejected. So I won’t. That still makes me more professional than Lenovo.The only thing Lenovo does well is build laptops (they’re great), and apologize for all the things they fail to do.Customer service? Zero out of ten. If it hadn’t been “just €59”, I would’ve taken legal action — because by law, any online order should be returnable within 14 days. But not with Lenovo.Never, ever again."
Al Geransar,2025-12-23,"Excellent Customer Service – Out-of-Warranty Repair HonoredI want to share a positive experience I had with Lenovo support.My Lenovo IdeaPad 1 15ALC7 suffered a complete motherboard failure just over a year after purchase, which was obviously very disappointing. The laptop would not power on at all, and the issue was diagnosed as a failed motherboard.Despite the device being out of warranty, Lenovo agreed to have the laptop picked up, assessed, and ultimately repaired at no cost. Throughout the process, communication was clear, professional, and respectful, and my concerns around data privacy were handled properly.Lenovo even allowed a full Windows reinstallation during service to ensure privacy, which I appreciated. The laptop has now been returned fully repaired and working.While the initial failure was frustrating, Lenovo’s willingness to stand behind their product and resolve the issue fairly has left me with a very positive impression of their customer service. Credit where it’s due, they handled this very well."
Marilyn Hartman,2025-12-23,"I bought my computer from Lenovo 5 years ago and used the ""trade in"" service in good faith. It's a scam. They said my screen was cracked, it definitely was not. I got a fraction of what their initial estimate was, if I ever get the refund. My computer was in perfect condition, it was simply old. Lenovo should be ashamed to use such a scam service as ""PyxTrade"". You are better off donating the computer to a church or school or needy person. I'm disgusted!"
Samayyah Williams,2025-12-22,"Poor support - Corel Perpetual LicenseThe customer service people are very nice, but Lenovo is not a good company that doesn't fulfill their promises and can/will steal your money. When I bought my laptop, I also purchased a perpetual license for this drawing software. It was a struggle to get the software and activate the license to begin with. Lenovo provided an activation key, which Corel did not recognize. I had to make a few phone calls to Lenovo and Corel and was finally able to get perpetual license going. Once the first year was up, the license was supposed to renew but it didn't. I called Corel and they pointed out that Lenovo was the one who offered that license and therefore they were the ones who had to resolve the issue. I called Lenovo Aug 30, 2025 with the promise they would fix it within 24-48 hours. It is now Dec 22, 2025 and the problem is still not fixed. Every time I called, Lenovo said the same thing: problem will be fixed with 24-48 hours. I called again, asking for a refund. But because it is outside the refund window (i.e. 1 year), Lenovo cant give a refund. The license was for 1 year, which intentionally put me outside of the return window. So Lenovo basically just took my money and ran. If they offer any kind of permanent or perpetual license, be warned. Lenovo probably cant help you and they wont try to help you."
